So I've been thinking, especially after reading some of the Warhammer related pastes, is that we always focus on the Skaven when writing these little short stories. It dawned on me however that if we were already going to bend lore in such a way to allow for furry women, why not just add particular species to each of the factions that would make some kind of sense. Canines of various types, from wolves to dogs, would certainly follow the races of men wherever they go be it Sigmarite Empire to the barbarous tribes of Norsca and even the Warriors of Chaos. Brettonias love of horses might transfer over to just loving horse anthros so a lot of the nobility is knightly humans and equine maidens. Maybe even the elves and dwarfs get in on with certain species being closely related to them. Cats being universal among all Elves even if the type of cat changes, and maybe badgers or mole for the dwarfs. Just something I've been pondering as I paint Eldar of all things while in quarantine.
